        public static Appointment isScheduleConflict​(int id,
                                             java.time.LocalDateTime start,
                                             java.time.LocalDateTime end)
                                      throws java.sql.SQLException
        Takes Customer ID, start and end date/times and tests if that customer has any conflicting appointments between start and end.
        Parameters:
        id - Customer ID for retrieving all appointments for that customer
        start - date/time that is to be tested if there is a conflict or not
        end - date/time that is to be tested if there is a conflict or not
        Returns:
        true if conflict, false if no conflict
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException

      • appointmentByType

        public static javafx.collections.ObservableList<Appointment> appointmentByType​(java.lang.String type)
                                                                        throws java.sql.SQLException
        Takes type and populates an ObservableList of all appointments of that Type. Lambda expression used here for the purpose of increased readability along with one less ObservableList used than a previous implementation with a for loop iterating through all appointments and populating a second list if the type's matched
        Parameters:
        type - String value type of an appointment object
        Returns:
        ObservableList of all appointments of specified type

        java.sql.SQLException
